# ERP Progress Audit Report

This progress audit report provides an objective, evidence-based analysis of the College ERP system's codebase compared against the Software Requirements Specification (SRS). It evaluates database schemas, API routes, and page implementations to estimate completion, identify gaps, and outline future development priorities.

---

## 1. Overall Completion Estimate

- **Estimated Completion Percentage**: **~60%**
  - **Core Foundation & Identity**: ~90% complete.
  - **Onboarding & Assignments**: ~90% complete.
  - **Timetable & Leaves/Proxy**: ~85% complete.
  - **Marks & Evaluations**: ~40% complete (schema exists, but write paths and V1/V2 engine logic are missing).
  - **Missing Core Modules** (Exam Seating, Secure Paper Gen, Audit Logging): ~5% complete (schema only, zero logic).
- **Current Project Maturity Level**: **Core Foundation Ready**
  - The architectural foundation is extremely robust, using a state-of-the-art tech stack (Next.js 16, React 19, Tailwind CSS v4, HeroUI v3, Drizzle ORM, Neon Postgres, Upstash, Brevo for email, and Convex for notifications).
  - All basic workflows (authentication, multi-role RBAC, profile onboarding, dynamic assignments, and leave requests) are highly functional.

