## 7. Potential Risk Areas

> [!WARNING]
> ### 1. Lack of Audit Trail (Security & Compliance)
> With no active logging inside the `audit_logs` table, administrative and faculty activities—including marks editing, HOD overrides, role promotions, and invite resends—occur without a system log. This is a severe compliance risk in an educational ERP.

> [!CRITICAL]
> ### 2. Evaluation Mutability
> The in-place upsert of internal evaluations exposes finalized grades to potential manipulation, as there is no immutable V1 layer to verify V2 modifications against.

> [!CAUTION]
> ### 3. Seating Generator Race Conditions
> Generating a classroom seating plan requires complex sequential algorithms. If multiple admins trigger seating plans simultaneously or during division changes, it could cause database deadlocks or duplicate seat assignments if not wrapped in serializable database transactions.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> ### 4. S3 Document Encryption at Rest
> The SRS mandates that examination papers are strictly encrypted at rest and invisible even to HODs. Standard file uploads in AWS S3 or MinIO will require backend envelope encryption to prevent direct reads by infrastructure administrators.

